# SEO Best Practices for AI Search Era

## Core Principles

1. **Brand is the competitive advantage** - In the LLM search era, brand matters more than content, links, or technical SEO
2. **Information Retrieval Score** - If AI can't extract your content chunks and facts, you won't appear in LLM search results
3. **Content freshness is the strongest AI ranking signal** - Content updated within 30-90 days performs best
4. **Topical authority = Knowledge Graph + Information Graph** - Build complete topic coverage
5. **Site Focus** - Google evaluates your vector center point; scattered topics = weaker AI visibility

## Content Chunking for AI

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Clear content block structure
<article>
  <section className="fact-chunk">
    <h2>Core Features</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Feature Name</strong>: Description</li>
      <li><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free to use</li>
      <li><strong>Target Users</strong>: Students, developers, designers</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</article>
```

## Use `<strong>` Tags for Key Facts

```tsx
// ✅ Highlight key information with <strong> tags
<p>
  Our tool provides <strong>free</strong> online conversion,
  supports <strong>PDF, DOCX, TXT</strong> formats,
  with processing speed <strong>under 5 seconds</strong>.
</p>
```

## Content Freshness

- Update content within 30-90 days
- Add `last-modified` metadata
- Display freshness badges on content
- Auto-detect stale content (>90 days)

## Structured Data (Schema.org)

```typescript
// WebApplication Schema
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  name: tool.name,
  description: tool.description,
  applicationCategory: "UtilityApplication",
  offers: { "@type": "Offer", price: "0", priceCurrency: "USD" },
  provider: { "@type": "Organization", name: "GeeksKai" }
}
```

**Required schemas:**
- WebApplication for tools
- Organization for brand identity
- FAQ for common questions
- Breadcrumb for navigation

## Technical SEO Checklist

- [ ] TTFB < 200ms
- [ ] LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1
- [ ] Images optimized (WebP/AVIF)
- [ ] CDN and caching enabled
- [ ] Preload critical resources

## Brand Building

1. **Entity signals** - Real founder info, contact details, media mentions
2. **Core facts must be extractable** - Pricing, features, positioning, target users
3. **Organization schema** - Legal name, founding date, contact points

## Page Structure

```tsx
// ✅ Correct heading hierarchy
<article>
  <h1>Main Title - Include Core Keywords</h1>
  <section>
    <h2>Main Section</h2>
    <h3>Subsection</h3>
    <h4>Detailed Topic</h4>
  </section>
